{"key":"processedPost-10920156","value":{"id":10920156,"first":10919541,"last":10923291,"when":1251058790,"utime":"08/23/09 11:19 PM","content":"Actually, until the last dozen or so years ago, cotton was the filter of choice for grain jars, autoclave bags, and liquid culture vials.&nbsp; It must be kept dry of course, but dry cotton will filter as well as polyfill.&nbsp; As said above, it's organic so if it gets wet, contaminants will attack it, but if kept dry it works fine.&nbsp; It was the only filter material we had when I got started, right up until PFTE filter disks came out in the mid-eighties.<br />RR","title":"Re: cotton ball subsitustion for polyfill"}}